3. Some important features of Spring Boot?

> The main aim of Spring Boot is to shorten code length and easily build web applications

  Spring Boot Can be used for all layers of application development
  
  It is lightweight considering the POJO model
  
  In Spring Boot we no need to deploy WAR files
  
  Allows loose coupling and easy testing

  It doesn't require XML configuration

  
  
4. Compare Spring vs Spring Web vs Spring Boot?


> Spring:
  ======
  Spring Framework is the most popular application development framework of Java. 
  The main feature of the Spring Framework is dependency Injection or Inversion of Control (IoC). 
  With the help of Spring Framework, we can develop a loosely coupled application.
  
  
>  SpringBoot:
   ===========
   
The main aim of Spring Boot is to shorten code length and easily build web applications
Spring Boot Can be used for all layers of application development
It is lightweight considering the POJO model
In Spring Boot we no need to deploy WAR files
Allows loose coupling and easy testing
It doesn't require XML configuration


> Spring Web:
  ===========
  
  Spring MVC is a model view controller-based web framework under the Spring framework.
  It provides ready to use features for building a web application.
  It specifies each dependency separately.
  It takes more time to achieve the productivity.
  
  
  
5. How to run spring boot application on customized port number (other than default 8080)  

> In src/main/resource, on application.properties just chnage the port number

server.port=8888;

 
